рҹ’… More Updates

В 
 * Llama Index Instrumentation: Llama Index is one of our first-class integrations. We have upgraded to the instrumentation module
   and are leaving the now deprecated callback handlers behind. Please upgrade to the instrumentation integration
   [https://langfuse.com/docs/integrations/llama-index/example-python-instrumentation-module].

 * GitHub Discussions in Docs: Github is where we centralize requests & questions about Langfuse.
   We've now integrated GitHub discussions deeply into our docs. Previews of all commonly asked questions and requests are
   included on their respective pages. See an example on our roadmap [https://langfuse.com/roadmap] page.

 * Langfuse Evals: Evals now supports any (tool-calling) LLM. Previously, only OpenAI models were supported. With this update, you
   can use any tool-calling LLM for evaluations. Langfuse will test the model with a sample run to ensure it works as expected.
   More here [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-10-11-extended-eval-models].


